title: Asset Quality Measures, Net Charge-Offs on All Loans and Leases, Secured by Real Estate, Single Family Residential Mortgages, Booked in Domestic Offices, Banks Not Among the 100 Largest in Size by Assets
notes: Charge-offs are the value of loans and leases removed from the books and charged against loss reserves. The 100 largest banks are measured by consolidated foreign and domestic assets.
